	"ART_faq_bets_q4": "What are the differences among Hong Kong, Malay, Indo and Euro odds type?",
	"ART_faq_bets_a4_1": "Hong Kong Odds identify the winning amount for every 1 unit that is staked. While the stake (and win amount) will be returned if the bet is successful, only the win amount is referenced in the odds. Maximum loss is the stake value.<br>Stake：1000，Odds：0.800，Win：800，Loss：-1000<br>Stake：1000，Odds：1.130，Win：1130，Loss：-1000",
	"ART_faq_bets_a4_2": "Malay Odds can be either positive or negative. Negative values identify the risk required to win one unit. Only after bet placement will be value related to the negative odds be deducted from your account, not the stake value displayed in Bet Slip. Negative odds will always display between 0 and -1.00.<br>Stake：1000，odds：0.800，Win：800，Loss：-1000<br>Stake：1000，Odds：-0.880，Win：1000，Loss：-880",
	"ART_faq_bets_a4_3": "Indo Odds can be either positive or negative. Negative values identify the risk required to win one unit. Only after bet placement will be value related to the negative odds be deducted from your account, not the stake value displayed in Bet Slip. Negative odds will always display a value higher than -1.00.<br>Stake：1000，Odds：1.130，Win：1130，Loss：-1000<br>Stake：1000，Odds：-1.250，Win：1000，Loss：-1250",
	"ART_faq_bets_a4_4": "Euro Odds identify the return amount for every 1 unit that is staked at these odds. If the bet is successful, the return will include both stake and winning amount. Maximum loss is the stake value.<br>Stake：1000，Odds：1.800，Win：800，Loss：-1000<br>Stake：1000, Odds：2.130，Win：1130，Loss：-1000",
