	"ART_faq_fs_q1": "What are Outrights?",
	"ART_faq_fs_a1": "Outright markets provide the opportunity to bet on the winner of an event, competition, tournament or race. They usually involve a single winner being declared, but dead-heat results may apply.",
	"ART_faq_fs_q2": "What is Dead Heat Rule?",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_1": "For markets where there is a dead heat with two or more winning selections in an event, the winnings will be reduced. This reduction is calculated by dividing the total stake by the number of selections of that dead heat. This reduced stake is then multiplied by the original odds to calculate the winnings. This part of the stake is then returned to the customer, together with any winnings. The other part of the stake is lost.",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_2": "For example:",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_3": "Stage 1 – You bet \u00245.00 on a selection at 16.0 (Potential winnings of \u002475.00)",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_4": "Stage 2 – Your selection is in a dead-heat with another selection both finishing in 1st place",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_5": "Stage 3 – Win/loss calculation: (Stake x Odd) / Number of Winners – Stake. Therefore the ‘Win / Loss’ is (\u00245.00 x 16.0) / 2 – \u00245.00 = \u002435.00.",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_6": "In the event of more than two selections finishing in a dead heat, the bets will be divided equally.",
	"ART_faq_fs_a2_7": "The Dead Heat Rules will not apply where, in our sole discretion, we consider an event winner can be determined on a points scored basis (for example from an event group stage).",

